n arborio rice has a longer cook time than other varieties. It absorbs liquid slowly while releasing its starches into the broth—what gives the risotto its creamy texture. \u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["10\" medium high-sided pan with lid","aluminum foil","baking sheet","8\" medium pot"],"id":7059,"ingredients":["cremini mushrooms","shallots","vegetable bouillon cube","porcini mushroom powder","Arborio rice","white wine","unsalted butter","chives","mascarpone cheese","shredded Gruyère cheese"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"cremini mushrooms","quantity":"10.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/326/medium_square_cremini-mushrooms-test2.jpg"},{"name":"shallots","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/130/medium_square_SHALLOT_copy.jpg"},{"name":"vegetable bouillon cube","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2377/medium_square_VEGETABLE_BOUILLON_CUBE_copy.jpg"},{"name":"porcini mushroom powder","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"teaspoon","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/548/medium_square_mushroom_powder.jpg"},{"name":"Arborio rice","quantity":"0.75","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/322/medium_square_rice-arborio.jpg"},{"name":"white wine","quantity":"0.25","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/256/medium_square_WHITE_WINE_copy.jpg"},{"name":"unsalted butter","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"packet","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2371/medium_square_medium_square_butter-test.jpg"},{"name":"chives","quantity":"0.125","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/242/medium_square_chives-2-test.jpg"},{"name":"mascarpone cheese","quantity":"4.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1501/medium_square_MASCARPONE_CHEESE_copy.jpg"},{"name":"shredded Gruyère cheese","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2322/medium_square_shredded-cheese-moz.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":["olive oil","kosher salt","black pepper"],"pantry_items_full":[{"name":"olive oil","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":null,"displayOrder":11,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/267/medium_square_olive-oil-test.jpg"},{"name":"kosher salt","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":12,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/473/medium_square_kosher-salt.jpg"},{"name":"black pepper","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":13,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/493/medium_square_spice-black-pepper-test.jpg"}],"steps":[{"title":"Prepare ingredients and warm broth","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69143/recipe_card_size_rtUEzI1zR5e9XrFq3dY5_1._Prepare_Ingredients_and_Warm_Broth.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat oven to 425°F. Wipe \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e clean with a damp paper towel and thinly slice. Peel \u003cstrong\u003eshallots\u003c/strong\u003e and mince. In a medium high-sided pan, combine \u003cstrong\u003ebouillon cube\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eporcini mushroom powder \u003c/strong\u003e(see recipe tip), and \u003cstrong\u003e3.5 cups water\u003c/strong\u003e; bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Remove pan from heat and cover to keep warm until Step 4. \u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Roast mushrooms","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69145/recipe_card_size_jiwvBXkvRauRtMhA5GLV_2._Roast_Mushrooms.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eLine a baking sheet with foil, add \u003cstrong\u003e1 cup sliced mushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e, and toss with \u003cstrong\u003e2 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.125 teaspoon\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003esalt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Arrange in a single layer, spacing apart, and roast until lightly brown and crisp, 15-18 minutes. \u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Sauté shallots and toast rice","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69144/recipe_card_size_SrdwmvmnQDi8Ud3ed0QW_3._Saute_Aromatics_and_Toast_riCE.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile mushrooms roast, heat \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e in a medium pot over medium-high heat. When oil is shimmering, add \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of shallots\u003c/strong\u003e; sauté, stirring, until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add \u003cstrong\u003erice\u003c/strong\u003e; cook, stirring, until toasted and translucent, 2-3 minutes. (Toasting the rice adds a delicious nutty flavor and prevents it from absorbing liquid too quickly). \u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Simmer risotto","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69146/recipe_card_size_LfuljHxyRkSkExr0ZZAg_4._Simmer_Risotto.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eAdd \u003cstrong\u003ewhite wine\u003c/strong\u003e to pot with rice, still over medium-high heat, and simmer until liquid is mostly absorbed, 1-2 minutes. Then, stir in \u003cstrong\u003ewarmed broth\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003e.5 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e, reserving pan. Increase heat under pot to high and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium high and simmer, stirring occasionally, until liquid is mostly absorbed and rice is tender, 15-20 minutes more (see recipe tip). \u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Sauté mushrooms","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69147/recipe_card_size_Tkc0cop6QxOkZKtSbDcE_5._Saute_Mushrooms.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile risotto simmers, heat \u003cstrong\u003ebutter\u003c/strong\u003e in pan from broth over medium-high heat. When butter is foamy, add \u003cstrong\u003eremaining mushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eremaining shallots\u003c/strong\u003e; sauté, stirring, until browned and tender, 10-12 minutes. Season with \u003cstrong\u003e.5 teaspoon salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003epepper \u003c/strong\u003eas desired. Remove pot from heat. Meanwhile, rinse \u003cstrong\u003echives\u003c/strong\u003e and thinly slice. In a small bowl, stir together \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of chives\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon mascarpone\u003c/strong\u003e to combine. \u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Plate mushroom risotto","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/69148/recipe_card_size_NtylB4RtRAixbZzDNhnz_6._Plate.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eTo pot with risotto, stir in \u003cstrong\u003eGruyère\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003esautéed\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003e3 tablespoons plain mascarpone \u003c/strong\u003e(save remainder for a snack) to combine. Divide \u003cstrong\u003emushroom\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003erisotto\u003c/strong\u003e between serving bowls. Dollop over \u003cstrong\u003echive mascarpone\u003c/strong\u003e. Top with \u003cstrong\u003eroasted\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eremaining\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003echives\u003c/strong\u003e. Dig in!\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian"